<Placemark>
  <name>Yellow Dog Falls / McCormick Wilderness Access</name>
  <styleUrl>#Hike / Boat / Walk-in</styleUrl>
  <description><![CDATA[<b>Category:</b> Backcountry / wilderness camping access<br/><b>Status:</b> Official wilderness access point<br/><b>Confidence:</b> High<br/><b>Fee:</b> No fee<br/><b>Reservation:</b> None noted<br/><b>Water:</b> Potable water not available<br/><b>Toilet:</b> None noted<br/><b>Access:</b> Trailhead off Ford Road on the McCormick Wilderness boundary; trail to falls is about 2.38 miles and unmarked in wilderness sections.<br/><b>Vehicle Note:</b> Drive-in to trailhead, then hike. Camping here is low-impact wilderness camping rather than a developed campground.<br/><b>Notes:</b> Official Ottawa pages say camping in McCormick Wilderness is part of the experience, campers should pack in water and pack out trash, and the forest enforces a 16-day camping limit.<br/><b>Primary Source URL:</b> https://www.fs.usda.gov/r09/ottawa/recreation/mccormick-wilderness<br/><b>Secondary Source URL:</b> https://www.fs.usda.gov/r09/ottawa/recreation/yellow-dog-falls]]></description>
  <Point><coordinates>-87.97516667,46.73363889,0</coordinates></Point>
</Placemark>
</Folder><Folder><name>Caution / Excluded</name>
<Placemark>
  <name>Brownstone Boat Launch</name>
  <styleUrl>#Caution / Excluded</styleUrl>
  <description><![CDATA[<b>Category:</b> Caution / excluded<br/><b>Status:</b> Do not treat as active boondocking pin<br/><b>Confidence:</b> Medium<br/><b>Fee:</b> $0 historically reported<br/><b>Reservation:</b> None noted<br/><b>Water:</b> None noted<br/><b>Toilet:</b> Pit toilet historically reported<br/><b>Access:</b> Boat-launch access off M-28 at Au Train Bay.<br/><b>Vehicle Note:</b> Easy enough to reach, which is probably part of why rules tightened up.<br/><b>Notes:</b> Campendium’s newer review reports a large “no overnight parking” sign despite older overnight-use reviews. Good example of why boat launches are boondocking traps.<br/><b>Primary Source URL:</b> https://www.campendium.com/brownstone-boat-launch<br/><b>Secondary Source URL:</b> https://outdoormichigan.org/feature/11060]]></description>
  <Point><coordinates>-86.8873,46.4467,0</coordinates></Point>
</Placemark>
